# Design system (Tailwind v4)

Entry point: `src/styles/app.css` (`@import "tailwindcss"`, `@theme`, `@utility`).

See also `code-conventions.mdc` for token hygiene (prefer Tailwind defaults when values match 1:1).

## Tokens over magic values

- Colors from `@theme`: `bg-neutral-0`, `text-neutral-600`, `bg-gold-500`, `border-neutral-200` — not `bg-[#2c2c2c]`, not `text-[rgb(...)]`.
- Fonts: `font-heading`, `font-body` — not inline `font-family`.
- When a theme utility exists: `text-ui`, `shadow-1` — not `text-[15px]`, not `shadow-[0_2px_8px_...]`.
- Typography: prefer `text-xs`, `text-sm`, `text-base`, `text-lg` for standard sizes; keep `text-ui`, `text-h4`, fluid `text-h1`–`text-display-xl` for brand-only sizes.

## Custom utilities in CSS, not in components

Repeatable patterns → `@utility` or shared `*ClassName.ts`:

- Typography helpers: `t-display`, `t-h1`, `t-body`, `t-ui`, …
- Layout: `container` (fluid gutter via `px-gutter`)
- Motion states: `.motion-fill-surface`, `.motion-fill-chevron` (minimal global CSS)

Do not duplicate these rules in `<style>` tags or long arbitrary values across many files.

Component-level class maps live in `src/components/ui/*ClassName.ts` and `src/components/product/*ClassName.ts`.

## When arbitrary values are OK

Allowed when **no** named utility exists in theme:

- precise layout: `px-[30px]`, `top-[36%]`
- one-off typography: `tracking-[0.06em]`, `text-[10px]` on carousel badges
- `color-mix(...)` referencing a token, not a raw hex

Before adding `[...]`, check `suggestCanonicalClasses` — e.g. `text-lg` instead of `text-[18px]`.

## Styling in components

- **Tailwind classes only** in `className` — no `<style>`, no inline `style=""` (exception: rare dynamic values from JS, e.g. motion transforms).
- Complex class sets → `cn()` from `src/lib/cn.ts` or dedicated `*ClassName.ts` exports.
- Button/card variants → `Record<Variant, string>` maps (e.g. `buttonClassName.ts`, `askRowClassName.ts`).

## React

- Attribute: `className` — not `class`.
- Conditional classes: `cn("base", isActive && "active", className)` — not string concatenation.
- `tailwind-merge` via `cn()` resolves conflicts when props override classes.
